<P>
   PHONEBANK-POLITICS (Houston) _ From the fourth floor of a
nondescript office building in suburban Houston a collection of
minimum-wage earners are on the frontlines of the battle for the
Republican presidential nomination, lobbing telephone calls into
South Carolina in an effort to elect George W. Bush. By Jim
Yardley.
</P>
<P>
   SC-POLITICS (Columbia, S.C.) _ On Bush and McCain. By Richard L.
Berke.
</P>
<P>
