<P>
   BBN-REDS-GRIFFEY (Undated) _ Ken Griffey Jr. still has a smile
fit for a prom king, broad and beaming. He donned the billed crown
of the Cincinnati Reds the other day and grinned: Hometown kid
eschews the biggest dollars to sign with his hometown team. It's
more complicated than that. Jim Bowden, the Reds general manager,
skillfully negotiated a staggeringly one-sided deal for one of the
greatest players in history. But Bowden has adopted a future
covered with personality land mines. On Baseball Column by Buster
Olney.
