<P>
   FBN-LANDRY-REMEMBER (Undated) _ To his players, to his
colleagues in National Football League and to the state of Texas,
longtime Dallas Cowboys Coach Tom Landry was a father figure, a
football innovator, even the gentlemanly and noble symbol that
helped buoy Texans at a time when a state's identity seemed all too
wrapped in the stigma of the assassination of President Kennedy.
``He conducted himself with such dignity and poise, it set the
example for how you should live your life,'' Charlie Waters, a
Cowboys safety for 11 seasons said of his former coach, who died of
leukemia Saturday night. By Bill Pennington.
</P>
<P>
   DOG-WESTMINSTER (New York) _ It worked for Michael Jordan. Why
not a triumphant comeback for Ch. Tryst of Grandeur? The 9-year-old
black Afghan hound, who did not compete in 1997 and 1998, is back
with a vengeance at the 124th Westminster Kennel Dog Show. By
Richard Sandomir.
</P>
