<P>
   CUBA-TRAVEL (Havana) _ Hundreds of Cuban families are stuck in a
limbo of politics and bureaucracy, holding valid documents for
travel to the United States that remain useless until they can get
exit visas from their government. By David Gonzalez.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-UNREST (Kosovska Mitrovica, Yugoslavia) _ Grenade
explosions and gunfire in the tense, ethnically divided city of
Kosovska Mitrovica injured seven residents and two French soldiers
on Sunday, U.N. police said. (Summary from wires.) By Carlotta
Gall.
</P>
<P>
   TERMLIMITS (Columbus, Ohio) _ As term limits gradually take
effect in 18 state legislatures across the country, the time
strictures so popular with voters are turning seasoned leadership
out of office, nipping political careers, and prompting unusual
party maneuvers. A new sort of fast-forward politicking spawned by
term limits is exemplified here in Ohio where the majority
Republican leadership is attempting to name three different
statehouse speakers across the next three years in advance of term
limits that start with the elections this November. By Francis X.
Clines.
</P>
<P>
   PHONEBANK-POLITICS (Houston) _ From the fourth floor of a
nondescript office building in suburban Houston a collection of
minimum-wage earners are on the frontlines of the battle for the
Republican presidential nomination, lobbing telephone calls into
South Carolina in an effort to elect George W. Bush. By Jim
Yardley.
</P>
<P>
   OBIT-SCHULZ (Undated) _ ``Peanuts'' creator Charles M. Schulz
died Saturday night, turning his farewell note in Sunday papers
into an epitaph for both a comic strip and its creator. Schulz was
77.
</P>
<P>
   WINDOWS-2000 (Menlo Park, Calif.) _ On the eve of the official
release of Windows 2000, Microsoft's first new business-oriented
operating system in four years, the software giant is endeavoring
to switch business users, large and small, to a new, more powerful
operating system that it says offers a host of benefits. But last
week, a growing rumbling among early users and analysts suggested
that Windows 2000 might not be a runaway success. By John Markoff.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-BUICK (La Jolla, Calif.) _ On the final round of the Buick
Invitational. By Clifton Brown.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
