<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Monday, Feb. 14 and thereafter. For questions about stories, please
contact Dennis Liff at the Daily News at (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   RAMPART-HEWITT (Los Angeles) _ Despite blood-spattered walls and
compelling evidence gathered by police, the Los Angeles County
District Attorney's Office refused to prosecute corrupt former
Rampart cop Brian Hewitt, who was fired for a vicious stationhouse
beating, a Los Angeles Daily News investigation has learned. By
Greg Gittrich and Beth Barrett. (Will move in the ``a'' national
