<P>
   RAMPART-ACCOUNT (Los Angeles) _ From the LAPD sergeant who got
the initial report that Rampart Officer Brian Hewitt viciously beat
a handcuffed prisoner right up to the day that Chief Bernard Parks
fired the cop, the LAPD vigorously and professionally investigated
the case. Hewitt, however, was never prosecuted. Here is a detailed
account of the case. By Greg Gittrich and Beth Barrett. (Will move
in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   BANKROB (Los Angeles) _ For three hours, the nation sat glued to
the TV watching two heavily armed men wearing body armor take on
police after robbing a North Hollywood bank. And then it watched as
robber Emil Matasareanu lay bleeding while police stood by. On
Tuesday, a federal civil jury will begin to hear evidence about
whether police deliberately denied Matasareanu medical aid. By
Jesse Hiestand. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n''
