<HEADLINE>
RAIN CANCELS PEPPERDINE-MISSOURI FINALE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HEATHER GRIPP  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   MALIBU, Calif. _ The Missouri baseball team was in the outfield
warming up minutes before the scheduled noon start of Sunday's game
at Pepperdine.
</P>
<P>
   Practice is all the Tigers got to do, though. The game was
cancelled because of rain.
</P>
<P>
   Even though the tarp was never removed from the infield, and one
of the Missouri coaches said he wasn't sure where Pepperdine's team
was, the Tigers wanted to get in a workout before they left.
</P>
<P>
   The players began to pack their bags as the rain intensified an
hour later. Even if the rain let up, the Tigers said there would
not be enough time to get in a game before their scheduled flight
home.
</P>
<P>
   If or when the game will be made up was not certain since
Pepperdine and Missouri are not scheduled to meet again this
season.
</P>
<P>
   The Waves (3-5) beat Missouri (0-2) in the first two games of
the series.
</P>
<P>
   Pepperdine's next game is Tuesday at Cal Poly. The Waves return
home for a three-game series against California starting Friday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
